I installed a hacked version of the SourceCodePro nerd font.
  https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts/releases/download/v3.0.2/SourceCodePro.zip
  Unzip and copy to ~/.local/share/fonts to new name (using Extra Light version)
  fc-cache -f -v

I had to use a PPA for Neovim
  sudo add-apt-repository ppa:neovim-ppa/unstable
I had to manually install FZF
  git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/junegunn/fzf.git ~/.fzf
  ~.fzf/install
I had to install a clipboard thing on my Laptop
  sudo apt install xclip


